## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

> Specify measurable constraints on system behavior — not what it does, but how well it does it.

| Category | Requirement | Target |
|----------|-------------|--------|
| Performance | [e.g., API response time] | [e.g., p99 < 200ms under 1000 RPS] |
| Security | [e.g., authentication method] | [e.g., OAuth 2.0, no plaintext credentials] |
| Scalability | [e.g., concurrent users] | [e.g., support 10,000 concurrent sessions] |
| Availability | [e.g., uptime SLA] | [e.g., 99.9% monthly uptime] |
| Data Retention | [e.g., log retention] | [e.g., 90-day rolling window] |
| Compliance | [e.g., GDPR, SOC 2] | [e.g., PII must be encrypted at rest] |

